    Step 3: raw sample audit, master rename, cleaning plan
    
    Audit our own pXRF sample workbooks before any cleaning (read-only;
    nothing in data/ was modified apart from the rename below).
    
    Coverage:
    - The master workbook is a strict SUBSET of the session files: all 1227
      of its readings trace back to an original machine file, and 0 rows
      exist only in the master.
    - 518 of 1745 distinct session readings were excluded, 515 correctly
      (other projects on the same instrument: Caesarea bronze, Tel Tsaf
      pottery, System Checks; plus 143 unlabelled Mining rows whose
      chemistry is carbonate, not obsidian).
    - Recovered one lost Motza object (readings 1489/1490, Excel rows
      832-833 of Avishai_Obsidian 12.2017.xlsx) hidden by the label typo
      "obidian". Decided: keep 1489 flagged low-quality, drop 1490 (author
      had annotated its Time cell "Invalid"; 81s run, light-element beam
      never completed). Confirmed row 1790 stays out: Rb/Zr/Nb all <LOD.
    
    Key facts for cleaning:
    - Reading No is NOT unique (counter reset; 94 numbers repeat across
      2017/2018). Key on Reading No + Time, with a fallback for the 3 rows
      whose Time is blank or annotated.
    - Usable elements: Rb/Zr/Nb ~99%. Sr 5.4%, Ba 4.7%, Y/Ga/Th absent.
    - 1227 readings are ~521 objects (dorsal/ventral pairs), so sample size
      is 521, not 1227.
    - Prefer element ratios: absolute Rb drifts with Bal, Rb/Zr does not.
    
    Rename data/samples/data manipulation.xlsx ->
    obsidian_pxrf_master_2017-2018.xlsx (contents untouched; the frozen
    Analysis with GitHub Copilot/ folder deliberately keeps the old name).
    
    Two claims corrected after checking them against the data: row 1790's
    removal is justified (judge readings by whether Rb/Zr/Nb were measured,
    not by duration), and Bal is NOT a beam-coverage proxy (it is the
    unidentified balance, mostly oxygen; no clean relation to `cover`).
    
    Adds analysis/02_map_raw_samples.py (reproduces the audit),
    docs/raw_sample_data_map_and_quality.md, docs/cleaning_plan.md.
    
